==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Jura-trias
<hw>Ju`ra-tri"as</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A term applied to many American Mesozoic strata, in which the
characteristics of the Jurassic and Triassic periods appear to be
blended.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Ju`ra-tri*as"sic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jurdiccion</ent>⟦br⟧
